playwright selectors https://playwright.dev/python/docs/locators

https://playwright.dev/python/docs/locators

to get selectors go to console.
then playwright.$("locatior")
to get all matching selectors
playwright.$$

playwright recommends to use locator strategy

page,locator.action
example:

page.locator("text=login").click()

this is to universalize the playwright for all language


nearby selectors

chaining selectors
    we can use 2 or more selectors to locate element
playwright.$("loginheadline_SM_ROOT_COMP28" class="jysNN">Log In</h1>)


assertions with playwright

in playwright
expect(page.locator("").to_be_visible)

